COMMUNITY GUIDELINES

These Community Guidelines apply to the Flight Star mobile application and any related features, content, and services operated by MS Software Solutions, LLC (“Flight Star,” “Company,” “we,” “us,” or “our”).

Flight Star is a platform intended for subjective, opinion-based feedback about professional interactions in the aviation industry. These Community Guidelines explain what users may and may not do on the platform, how content may be moderated, and what enforcement actions may be taken.

By accessing or using Flight Star, you agree to comply with these Community Guidelines. If you do not agree, you must not use the application.

1. Purpose of the Platform
Flight Star is designed to allow users to share general, subjective impressions and opinions regarding professional interactions. Flight Star is not a reporting system, investigative platform, public accusation forum, safety hotline, employment screening tool, disciplinary system, or regulatory complaint channel.

Users must not use Flight Star to make or spread factual allegations, retaliate against others, interfere with employment relationships, or post content that could reasonably create legal, privacy, safety, or reputational harm.

2. General Standards
All content submitted to Flight Star must be:
•	based on the user’s own experience or opinion,
•	framed in general and subjective terms,
•	respectful of privacy and safety,
•	non-retaliatory,
•	non-threatening,
•	and compliant with applicable law.

We may remove or restrict any content that, in our judgment, creates legal risk, safety risk, privacy risk, or misuse of the platform.

3. What You May Post
Users may post content that reflects their own personal, subjective impressions of a professional interaction on Flight Star, including:
•	star ratings based on personal opinion,
•	general impressions of professionalism,
•	subjective impressions of communication style,
•	subjective impressions of leadership style,
•	subjective impressions of crew resource management,
•	subjective impressions of decision making in a general sense,
•	subjective impressions of technical proficiency in a general sense,
•	and broad, constructive, non-identifying feedback.

All permitted content must:
•	be based on the user’s own experience,
•	be framed as opinion rather than fact,
•	remain generalized and non-specific,
•	avoid identifying incident details,
•	and not include prohibited allegations, medical claims, safety claims, legal conclusions, or confidential information.

4. Prohibited Content
The following content is prohibited and may result in removal, suspension, or permanent ban.

A. Safety, Legal, Regulatory, or Criminal Allegations
You may not post content alleging or implying:
•	safety violations,
•	near-misses,
•	FAA, ICAO, company, or regulatory violations,
•	criminal conduct,
•	illegal conduct,
•	substance use or impairment,
•	intoxication,
•	or any other legal or regulatory misconduct.

B. Medical, Mental Health, or Employment-Related Claims
You may not post or imply:
•	mental health conditions,
•	medical conditions,
•	disability status,
•	substance abuse history,
•	drug or alcohol testing history,
•	disciplinary action,
•	training failures,
•	checkride failures,
•	termination status,
•	leave status,
•	or any other employment or medical information.

C. Identifying, Traceable, or Confidential Information
You may not post:
•	employee numbers,
•	specific flight numbers,
•	specific dates or times,
•	specific city pairs tied to incidents,
•	internal airline communications,
•	schedules,
•	crew lists,
•	screenshots of internal systems,
•	confidential, proprietary, or non-public information,
•	or details that could reasonably identify a specific incident beyond a generalized opinion.

D. Harassment, Abuse, and Privacy Violations
You may not post:
•	threats,
•	intimidation,
•	hate speech,
•	slurs,
•	discriminatory content,
•	sexually harassing content,
•	doxxing,
•	stalking,
•	retaliation,
•	blackmail,
•	coercion,
•	or content intended to humiliate, punish, or damage another person.

E. False, Misleading, or Manipulative Content
You may not:
•	impersonate another person,
•	create fake accounts,
•	submit misleading reviews,
•	coordinate review campaigns,
•	manipulate ratings,
•	evade moderation,
•	repost removed content,
•	or use the platform to manufacture a false impression about any person or group.

F. Misuse of the Platform
You may not use Flight Star:
•	to influence hiring, firing, discipline, upgrade, or scheduling decisions,
•	to build dossiers or investigative files on individuals,
•	to support grievances, disputes, or retaliation efforts,
•	to collect data on users or crew for off-platform use,
•	to scrape or systematically extract content,
•	or to compete with or commercially exploit the platform without written permission.

5. Private Notes
If Flight Star offers a private notes feature, that feature is provided only for the user’s own personal organizational use.

Private notes remain subject to these Community Guidelines. You may not use private notes to store unlawful, defamatory, discriminatory, threatening, privacy-invasive, retaliatory, or otherwise improper content. We reserve the right to restrict or remove access to features, including private notes, in response to misuse or legal risk.

6. Screenshots and Off-Platform Sharing
Users may not screenshot, record, copy, share, repost, or distribute content from Flight Star outside the platform without authorization. However, users acknowledge that we cannot control off-platform conduct by third parties. Any content posted to the platform may be copied or shared by others in violation of these rules, and users assume that risk when posting.

7. Reporting Content
Users may report content believed to violate these Community Guidelines through any reporting tools we make available or by contacting support.

Submitting a report does not guarantee review, removal, or any particular outcome. We review reports in our discretion and may take action, decline action, or request additional information.

Abuse of reporting tools, including false, retaliatory, or bad-faith reports, may itself result in enforcement action.

8. Requests from Individuals Referenced on the Platform
A person who believes content about them violates these Community Guidelines may request review through the reporting tools or by contacting support. We may require verification before reviewing such requests.

We may remove, restrict, leave up, or otherwise act on content in our sole discretion. Flight Star does not mediate personal disputes and does not guarantee removal upon request.

9. Moderation and Enforcement
Flight Star uses a hybrid moderation system that may include deterministic rule-based filters, keyword detection, policy-adjacency detection, AI-assisted classification, and human review by Company administration. Content may be screened before publication, after publication, or both.

Content that appears to involve safety allegations, legal or regulatory issues, medical or employment-sensitive information, identifying or traceable details, confidential or proprietary information, harassment, retaliation, discrimination, abusive conduct, or platform misuse may be automatically flagged, restricted, suppressed, delayed, or routed to manual review. Content may also be held for manual review where the system is uncertain, where context is incomplete, or where automated systems detect policy-adjacent risk.

Flight Star applies conservative moderation standards and may over-flag content in order to reduce legal, privacy, safety, confidentiality, and platform-integrity risk. As a result, some content may be delayed, restricted, suppressed, or removed even if a user believes the content is fair, accurate, or ultimately permissible.
Submitting content does not guarantee publication, continued visibility, restoration, or approval. Flight Star may remove content, limit visibility, disable accounts, preserve moderation records, and take additional enforcement action in its sole discretion.

10. Zero-Tolerance Violations
The following may result in immediate suspension or permanent ban:
•	safety allegations,
•	criminal allegations,
•	medical or mental health claims,
•	substance impairment claims,
•	doxxing or privacy violations,
•	threats or harassment,
•	retaliation or coercion,
•	impersonation,
•	ban evasion,
•	and coordinated abuse of the platform.

11. No Obligation to Host or Remove Content
We are not obligated to publish, keep, restore, or remove any particular content. We may take action on content or accounts at any time, with or without notice, where we believe such action is appropriate to protect the platform, users, third parties, or the Company.

Our decision to remove or not remove content does not mean that we agree with it, verify it, adopt it, or accept responsibility for it.

12. Platform Security and Misuse
You may not:
•	scrape or systematically collect data from the platform,
•	use bots, spiders, scripts, or automation without authorization,
•	interfere with platform security or functionality,
•	reverse engineer or attempt to extract source code except as allowed by law,
•	access accounts or data without authorization,
•	create accounts under false pretenses,
•	sell or transfer your account,
•	or use the platform in a way that disrupts service or harms other users.

13. Consequences of Violations
Violations of these Community Guidelines may result in warnings, content removal, feature restrictions, temporary suspensions, permanent bans, device-level bans, referral to service providers, or referral to law enforcement where appropriate.

We reserve all rights to take any lawful action we consider necessary to protect the platform, our users, third parties, and the Company.

14. Updates to These Guidelines
We may update these Community Guidelines from time to time. Continued use of Flight Star after any update constitutes acceptance of the revised Guidelines. If you do not agree to the updated Guidelines, you must stop using the application.

